An eligible member may elect to participate in the DROP for a period not to exceed the lesser of:
4 years;
the difference between 28 years and the member's eligibility service as of the date of the member's election to participate in the DROP and retire from the State Police Retirement System, if the member is a member of the State Police Retirement System on or before June 30, 2011; or
the difference between 29 years and the member's eligibility service as of the date of the member's election to participate in the DROP and retire from the State Police Retirement System, if the member becomes a member of the State Police Retirement System on or after July 1, 2011;
the difference between age 60 and the member's age as of the date of the member's election to participate in the DROP and retire from the State Police Retirement System; or
a term selected by the member.

Participation in the DROP ends if the DROP participant:
separates from employment in accordance with the binding letter of resignation submitted with the member's election form;
except for the Secretary of State Police, attains age 60;
dies;
is terminated from employment by the Maryland State Police at any time before the date specified on the member's election form;
shortens the time period for participation in the DROP by delivering to the Maryland State Police and the Board of Trustees written notice of the intent of the DROP member to terminate employment; or
accepts a special disability retirement allowance as provided in subsection (k) of this section.
